other_tests.findings: There is a 14 mm dilated tubular structure in the right lower quadrant in the expected region of the appendix with a hyperdensity within it suggestive of appendicolith. Additionally, a hyperdensity measuring 6 x 3 mm is noted at the base of this structure at the origin of the cecum suggestive of obstructing appendicolith. No evidence of free fluid or free air in the abdomen. The liver, gallbladder, stomach, visualized loops of small and large bowel, pancreas, bilateral adrenal glands, spleen, and bilateral kidneys are normal. No mesenteric or retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy by CT size criteria.
